-- J. Crew Agrees to Be Purchased by TPG, Leonard Green for $43.50 a Share
-- B y   H e a t h e r   B u r k e
-- 2010-11-23T15:42:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/j-crew-agrees-to-be-purchased-by-tpg-leonard-green-for-43-50-a-share.html
J. Crew Group Inc. agreed to be
purchased by funds affiliated with TPG Capital and
Leonard Green & Partners LP for $43.50 per share in cash, or
about $3 billion. The price represents a premium of 29 percent
to J. Crew’s average closing share price over the last month.  The agreement permits a special committee of J. Crew’s
directors to solicit, receive, evaluate and enter into
negotiations with respect to alternative proposals through
Jan.15. Millard Drexler will continue as chairman and chief
executive officer and maintain a significant equity investment
in J. Crew.  J. Crew also reported third-quarter earnings per share of
58 cents a share. The average analyst estimate in a Bloomberg
survey was 54 cents. The retailer cut its full-year forecast to
$2.08 to $2.13 a share from $2.25 to $2.35. The average analyst
estimate is $2.22.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Heather Burke at 
 hburke2@bloomberg.net  